text: Do state updates in chaincode (e.g. data passed to stub.PutState) get compressed on disk in any way? Put another way, if my chaincode compresses its own data will it benefit by being able to store more data?

Leaving compression up to the application seems like it would present problems in terms of determinism, especially where peers are deployed on heterogeneous platforms (e.g. some x86_64 peers and some ARM peers).
Anybody who has opinions on the logging format for the chaincode container and how it should be set please check out <https://jira.hyperledger.org/browse/FAB-1936> and add any comments.
